      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "My apologies for the oversight. Typically, the travel time between Marunouchi and Shibuya will be more of a 30-minute to 45-minute train ride depending on the lines and times picked. Let's refine Day 2 with more details.\n\n**Day 2: Shibuya & Surrounds (Expanded)**\n- Morning: You'll catch an Chiyoda Line train from Keikyu-Harajuku Station (approximately a 20-minute walk from Marunouchi) into Tokyo Station, then transfer to the Yurakucho Line, towards Shibuya Station (~35 minutes total). Shibuya Crossing Show works best in the morning, so make sure to hit there between 5:00 AM and 7:30 AM.\n- Breakfast: Savory surprise at Pankeyuu Daikuroku, renowned for its fluffy pancakes and smoothie shop.\n- Morning: Discover some architectural mazes in Aoyama, but be quick! (Brief visit of 30 minutes)\n- Shibuya Meeting: Head to a tranquil spot like \"Shibuya 109 Urban Loft,\" which offers a quiet upper floor dedicated to work environments (scheduled meeting from 10:00 AM to 12:00 PM).\n- Lunch:",
